{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": 1,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "This is the account of Shem, Ham and Japheth, Noah's sons, who themselves had sons after the flood."
        }
      ],
      "title": "The Japhethites",
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 2,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Japheth: Gomer, Magog, Madai, Javan, Tubal, Meshek and Tiras."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 3,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Gomer: Ashkenaz, Riphath and Togarmah."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 4,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Javan: Elishah, Tarshish, the Kittites and the Rodanites."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 5,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "From these the maritime peoples spread out into their territories by their clans within their nations, each with its own language."
        }
      ],
      "title": "The Hamites",
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 6,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Ham: Cush, Egypt, Put and Canaan."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 7,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Cush: Seba, Havilah, Sabtah, Raamah and Sabteka. The sons of Raamah: Sheba and Dedan."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 8,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Cush was the father of Nimrod, who became a mighty warrior on the earth."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 9,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He was a mighty hunter before the Lord; that is why it is said,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Like Nimrod, a mighty hunter before the Lord.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 10,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The first centers of his kingdom were Babylon, Uruk, Akkad and Kalneh, in Shinar."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 11,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "From that land he went to Assyria, where he built Nineveh, Rehoboth Ir, Calah"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 12,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and Resen, which is between Nineveh and Calah—which is the great city."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 13,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Egypt was the father of the Ludites, Anamites, Lehabites, Naphtuhites,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 14,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Pathrusites, Kasluhites (from whom the Philistines came) and Caphtorites."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 15,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Canaan was the father of Sidon his firstborn, and of the Hittites,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 16,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Jebusites, Amorites, Girgashites,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 17,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Hivites, Arkites, Sinites,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 18,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Arvadites, Zemarites and Hamathites. Later the Canaanite clans scattered"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 19,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "and the borders of Canaan reached from Sidon toward Gerar as far as Gaza, and then toward Sodom, Gomorrah, Admah and Zeboyim, as far as Lasha."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 20,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "These are the sons of Ham by their clans and languages, in their territories and nations."
        }
      ],
      "title": "The Semites",
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 21,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Sons were also born to Shem, whose older brother was Japheth; Shem was the ancestor of all the sons of Eber."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 22,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Shem: Elam, Ashur, Arphaxad, Lud and Aram."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 23,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sons of Aram: Uz, Hul, Gether and Meshek."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 24,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Arphaxad was the father of Shelah, and Shelah the father of Eber."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 25,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Two sons were born to Eber: One was named Peleg, because in his time the earth was divided; his brother was named Joktan."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 26,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Joktan was the father of Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 27,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 28,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Obal, Abimael, Sheba,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 29,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Ophir, Havilah and Jobab. All these were sons of Joktan."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 30,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The region where they lived stretched from Mesha toward Sephar, in the eastern hill country."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 31,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "These are the sons of Shem by their clans and languages, in their territories and nations."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 32,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "These are the clans of Noah's sons, according to their lines of descent, within their nations. From these the nations spread out over the earth after the flood."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}